{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015CfPXpCbTtifae3qT4ShrM","type":"tool_result","content":"# Complete Protocol for New Page/Screen Design\n\n## Step 0: Pre-flight Checks\n- Verify asset URLs match exactly as written in `llms.txt`—never construct or guess paths\n- After each fetch, confirm the response starts with expected content type (markdown, CSS, or JSON)\n- Stop immediately if you encounter HTML or 404 responses\n\n## Step 1: Design Brief Interview (Scale Gate)\nFetch `docs/design-system/design-brief.md` and apply its gatekeeping:\n- **New page/site with no existing DESIGN.md**: Complete 7-domain interview covering tone, look ownership, color, type, structure, interaction level, and content\n- **Small component fix**: Skip the full interview\n- **Project with existing DESIGN.md**: Never re-interview\n\nDocument all answers as the project's own `DESIGN.md`. In non-interactive environments, proceed with recommended defaults and list assumptions in your final report.\n\n## Step 2: Token Ownership & Fallback Rules\n- If the project has its own DESIGN.md, token SSOT, or established styling, derive all values from that foundation\n- Only fetch `tokens/tokens.css` when the project has no tokens *or* when explicitly requested\n- Never invent color or dimension values\n- Use `tokens/askewly.tokens.json` for reference only\n\n## Step 3: Pattern & Recipe Selection\n1. Fetch `docs/design-system/pattern-taxonomy.md` to identify the surface category (marketing, application UI, commerce, docs) and pattern groups\n2. From the llms.txt Recipes section, fetch every matching recipe\n3. Follow each recipe's Structure, Tokens, States, Checks, and Anti-patterns sections\n\n## Step 4: Composition & Principles\nFetch `docs/design-system/principles.md` and apply task-first hierarchy and meaningful motion when combining recipes into the complete page.\n\n## Step 5: Failure Mode Prevention\nFetch `docs/design-system/anti-patterns.md` to avoid generic-AI-output pitfalls.\n\n## Step 6: Mandatory Self-Judgment (Before Reporting)\nFetch `docs/design-system/style-signature.md` and evaluate your output:\n- All 5 operating principles met\n- Zero hard-fail dislikes\n- Include per-principle judgment in your report\n\n## Step 7: Verification Loop\n- Complete all interaction states (hover, focus, active, disabled, loading, error)\n- Test dark mode consistency\n- Confirm WCAG contrast compliance\n\n## Step 8: Human Verification Gate\nCapture screenshots (light/dark modes, key states) and attach to your report. **Do not declare work complete or deploy until the user reviews and confirms the output.**"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f1423542-66b2-49e0-a02f-d7685d2196fd","uuid":"422d6c40-c31c-420e-9a42-431fd49ce2b6","timestamp":"2026-07-18T14:51:24.140Z","tool_use_result":{"bytes":6190,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Complete Protocol for New Page/Screen Design\n\n## Step 0: Pre-flight Checks\n- Verify asset URLs match exactly as written in `llms.txt`—never construct or guess paths\n- After each fetch, confirm the response starts with expected content type (markdown, CSS, or JSON)\n- Stop immediately if you encounter HTML or 404 responses\n\n## Step 1: Design Brief Interview (Scale Gate)\nFetch `docs/design-system/design-brief.md` and apply its gatekeeping:\n- **New page/site with no existing DESIGN.md**: Complete 7-domain interview covering tone, look ownership, color, type, structure, interaction level, and content\n- **Small component fix**: Skip the full interview\n- **Project with existing DESIGN.md**: Never re-interview\n\nDocument all answers as the project's own `DESIGN.md`. In non-interactive environments, proceed with recommended defaults and list assumptions in your final report.\n\n## Step 2: Token Ownership & Fallback Rules\n- If the project has its own DESIGN.md, token SSOT, or established styling, derive all values from that foundation\n- Only fetch `tokens/tokens.css` when the project has no tokens *or* when explicitly requested\n- Never invent color or dimension values\n- Use `tokens/askewly.tokens.json` for reference only\n\n## Step 3: Pattern & Recipe Selection\n1. Fetch `docs/design-system/pattern-taxonomy.md` to identify the surface category (marketing, application UI, commerce, docs) and pattern groups\n2. From the llms.txt Recipes section, fetch every matching recipe\n3. Follow each recipe's Structure, Tokens, States, Checks, and Anti-patterns sections\n\n## Step 4: Composition & Principles\nFetch `docs/design-system/principles.md` and apply task-first hierarchy and meaningful motion when combining recipes into the complete page.\n\n## Step 5: Failure Mode Prevention\nFetch `docs/design-system/anti-patterns.md` to avoid generic-AI-output pitfalls.\n\n## Step 6: Mandatory Self-Judgment (Before Reporting)\nFetch `docs/design-system/style-signature.md` and evaluate your output:\n- All 5 operating principles met\n- Zero hard-fail dislikes\n- Include per-principle judgment in your report\n\n## Step 7: Verification Loop\n- Complete all interaction states (hover, focus, active, disabled, loading, error)\n- Test dark mode consistency\n- Confirm WCAG contrast compliance\n\n## Step 8: Human Verification Gate\nCapture screenshots (light/dark modes, key states) and attach to your report. **Do not declare work complete or deploy until the user reviews and confirms the output.**","durationMs":9310,"url":"https://ui.askewly.com/llms/docs/design-system/entry-protocol.md"}}
